  <h1>Shivamogga – Gateway to Malenadu’s Majesty</h1>
  <p>Shivamogga (formerly Shimoga), nestled on the banks of the Tunga River and encircled by the lush greenery of the Western Ghats, is a vibrant city renowned as the <strong>“Gateway of Malnad”</strong>—a scenic hill region in Karnataka. With its rich blend of history, heritage, hill stations, and waterfalls, this destination promises a perfect mix of nature, culture, and adventure.</p>

  <h1>Historical & Cultural Roots</h1>
  <ul>
    <li>The name “Shivamogga” is believed to derive from local folklore — “<em>Shiva‑Mukha</em>” (Face of Shiva) or “<em>Sihi‑Moge</em>” (Sweet Pot).</li>
    <li>The area holds archaeological significance with relics dating back to the Neolithic and Iron Age.</li>
    <li>Historically ruled by dynasties such as the Kadambas, Chalukyas, Hoysalas, Keladi Nayakas, and Vijayanagara Empire.</li>
    <li>Shivamogga is a cultural hub featuring institutions like Kuvempu University, vibrant Yakshagana dance-drama troupes, and cultural centers.</li>
  </ul>

  <h1>Top Attractions & Natural Wonders</h1>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Jog Falls:</strong> India’s second-highest plunge waterfall (approx. 253 meters), cascading in four segments amid lush surroundings.</li>
    <li><strong>Kodachadri:</strong> A heritage peak rising to 1,343 meters, offering breathtaking trekking trails and panoramic views of the Western Ghats.</li>
    <li><strong>Sakrebailu Elephant Camp:</strong> An interactive camp near Shivamogga where visitors can observe elephants bathing in the river.</li>
    <li><strong>Tyavarekoppa Safari Park:</strong> A wildlife reserve featuring lions and tigers, with jeep safari options.</li>
    <li><strong>Mandagadde Bird Sanctuary:</strong> A river island sanctuary home to thousands of migratory birds, especially active during monsoon.</li>
    <li><strong>Chandragutti Renukamba Temple:</strong> An ancient cave temple dedicated to Goddess Renuka, surrounded by scenic hills.</li>
    <li><strong>Keladi & Nearby Temples:</strong> Explore historical temples like Rameshwara and Aghoreshwara known for Hoysala architecture.</li>
  </ul>


